    ofNote: "Loag assassins: thought destroyed by Jedi, secretly rebuilt in hollowed volcano. Min 5,000 cr contracts. Cult of Those Who Redeem: secret Jedi-worshippers. Meris III pharmaceutical plant is key export. 'The Joining' land bridge ended 1,000-year war between Meris and Teltiors. | THE LOAG DAGGER (LOST RELIC): The symbol of the Loag — a 30-cm one-sided curved blackened blade with dark hide grip and a dark red ruby pommel — was the dagger upon which all Loag cultists swore their blood oath. A band of six Jedi Knights came to Merisee in the Old Republic era and broke the Loag's power in a year-long campaign; only three survived, and they took the dagger with them when they left Merisee, eventually depositing it in the Galactic Museum on Coruscant where it stayed as a reminder of Jedi service to the galaxy. Under the Empire, the dagger was kept on display as 'an example of how insurrectionists could threaten public order' (the Jedi referred to in the Imperial labels only as 'Servants of the Galactic Order'). When the New Republic recaptured Coruscant after the Empire's resurgence, the Loag Dagger was confirmed missing from the Imperial Museum looting inventory. The cult has secretly survived all this time and the Loag will stop at nothing to recover the dagger — partial confirmed rumors hold them responsible for at least three recent political murders in the New Republic era. (See Star Wars Planets Collection pp.159-160 for additional Merisee/Loag material.)"
