    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.33-35",
    summary: "Reuss VIII was once a lush, green planet known for scenic splendor and mild climate, a prime food producer for several colony worlds. The industrial giants of the Old Republic purchased vast tracts of land cheaply, and within a few years the planet was bought out from under the Reussi, the near-Human natives. Now the industrial juggernaut of Portmoak Sector, the entire land surface is covered with factories, refining plants, inefficient waste incinerators, and crumbling skyscrapers. The atmosphere is loaded with toxins and the rain is highly acidic. On low contamination days, exposure without a breath filter causes 2D damage per six hours; after two weeks, lung damage is irreversible without cybernetic replacement. On high contamination days, exposure without a full environment suit causes 2D+2 damage per round.",
    locations: "Industrial belts (so huge they merge into one another, leaving residential neighborhoods as small islands). Crumbling residential blocks (home to the desperately poor workforce). Waste incinerators (inefficient, contributing to toxic atmosphere).",
    ofNote: "The Reussi are effectively slaves of the Reuss Corporation with average life expectancy around 40 years, never seeing a single plant or growing thing. Rust Rats — mostly orphaned children — live hand-to-mouth in corroded buildings, slowly dying from acid burns and lung disease (all stats 1D except DEX 3D, pick pockets 5D, survival: Reuss VIII 5D). Major conduit for illegal goods smuggled to the Core Worlds. Crimelord Torel Vorne ensures customs regulations remain lax. Vorne's organ donation policy allows debtors to trade organs for credit forgiveness (up to 25,000 credits, surgery damage 1D-6D based on value). Located in Portmoak Sector."
