    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.80",
    summary: "Rordak is one of the Empire's most notorious prison worlds, rivaling the spice mines of Kessel for brutality. The native Viska are terrifying flying carnivores who feed on blood via a proboscis (blossug). They live in clusters of repulsorlift-powered flying cities reaching thousands of meters high, ruled by a caleisk monarch (chosen via children fighting to the death). The Empire uses orbital nightcloaks to block sunlight over prison camps, creating perpetual darkness. Prisoners are denied breath masks despite the toxic CO2 atmosphere, and are worked in barthierum mines or sold as slaves to Viska nobles. Air poisoning can cause paralysis, coma, and death.",
    locations: "Viska Flying Cities (repulsorlift-powered, thousands of meters high, multi-level: royals on top, workers on bottom). Prison Alpha TR-8 (5,452 prisoners, 150 guards, barthierum mine 500m away). 4 starports: Dreggusom, Azkulkt, Whosk, Deggaruls. Orbital nightcloaks over each prison camp.",
    ofNote: "Viska: flying carnivores, 2-3m body + 5m wingspan, feed via blossug proboscis (4D + 3D/minute blood drain). Infrared vision. Need 2 liters blood/day (3 liters from non-natives, causes 1D cumulative damage). Caleisk succession: all children fight to death, survivor rules. Prison camps: no breath masks, perpetual nightcloak darkness. CO2 atmosphere: Moderate stamina every 3 hours or air poisoning (paralysis → coma 1D days → possible death). Major Drummond: warden of Alpha TR-8, thin, cruel, cares only for money and cruelty."
