    majorImports: "Mid tech",
    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.86",
    summary: "Veron is a popular tourist world dominated by tropical rainforests and the Gazaran — friendly cold-blooded gliding reptiles who live in tree-top cities led by respected elder females. The fevvenor trees cover 75% of land mass, reaching 50 meters tall. The Gazaran never venture to ground level (too cold for their biology — penalties start at 30°C, hibernation below 10°C, death after 28 hours). Ground-level predators include gwerax-hai (tusked reptilian hunters), black behemoths, and swamp worms. Tourism drives the economy, with Trelbio Spaceport (40-story tower) as the main entry point. The Broken Trees Islands hide ancient Gazaran artifacts in shallow waters — smuggling them off-world is a cottage industry.",
    locations: "Trelbio Spaceport (40-story tower, hotels, restaurants, 30+ support buildings). Hengin Ki-Tapp Welt Gon-far (largest Gazaran city near Trelbio, 100K+ Gazaran). Burll-ikem-Tiz-Sah (largest city overall, 350K). Gazzt So-Terr Aggul Meztim-Si (50K, continent of Ganzka). Broken Trees Islands (ancient artifacts in shallow waters). Sileron (inner planet, hostile, extreme seasons). Trieran (outer planet, cool, oceanographic research bases).",
    ofNote: "Gazaran: cold-blooded gliding reptiles, led by elder females (must raise 12+ litters). Temperature sensitivity: -1D at 30°C, -2D at 25°C, -3D at 20°C, -4D below 15°C, hibernation below 10°C, death after 28 hours in cold. Glide 15m/round (standard grav). Extremely superstitious. All non-gliding visitors must wear repulsor belts. Ground-level predators: gwerax-hai (tusked, hunt in skulks of 5-15), black behemoths (ambush predators), swamp worms (poisonous tail 4D). Imperial Governor Ferlem Kie'hintack allows traditional Gazaran governance."
