    source: "WEG40063 Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim p.44-45",
    summary: "Epsi Nadir is a planet purchased outright by the Most Honourable Guild of Armourers, a guild of the galaxy's best weapons specialists dealing in extremely exotic and rare weaponry. The Guild obtains legal planetary waivers to sell restricted arms, classifying most weapons as 'collector's items' or 'historical artifacts.' Its auction house is located here, and once a year the Guild loads a liner with trade samples and heads to the galaxy's periphery, sending invitations to wealthy potential customers. Past customers include Boba Fett, Dengar, Zardra, and Matt Talon, along with crimelords, nobles, and corporate executives.",
    locations: "Guild Auction House (the most dangerous place in the galaxy to start a firefight — Boba Fett, IG-88, Zardra, and other hunters attend). Main Guildhouse (deep in the Core, dangerous for wanted individuals to visit).",
    ofNote: "The Guild has franchise deals with every major arms manufacturer and contacts with almost every minor company. If the Guild doesn't sell it, either it isn't made anymore or it's unknown technology. Recent auction lots have included a lightsaber (bidding exceeded 250,000 credits without reaching reserve), partial Mandalorian battle armor, and an assassin droid. Weapons registration documents can be 'lost' for a small under-the-table fee. The Guild may also be commissioned to obtain specific items for clients — Moff Balfour seeks a Kalld'n-c'dss stardrive for his yacht the Lady Akiko."
