    majorImports: "Various",
    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.121",
    summary: "Elrood is the capital of Elrood Sector, a backwater corner of the Metharian Nebula Territories. The planet is a bureaucratic world and headquarters of Radell Mining Corporation, the sector's largest company. The planet is strict and by-the-book — arriving ships face decontamination, manifest verification, pilot license checks, and engine emission inspections. Reputation matters greatly in Elrood Sector; newcomers face +1D difficulty on social skills until they prove themselves. The sector has two rival Imperial Star Destroyers (Stalker and Thunderflare) and is connected by the Elrood-Derilyn Trade Route (18 hours at x1 hyperdrive). The Coyn Route bypasses occupied Derilyn.",
    locations: "Elrood Starport (strict, by-the-book operations). Radell Mining Corporation HQ (largest employer in sector). Elrood-Derilyn Trade Route ('E-D Run', 18 hours at x1). Coyn Route (bypass around Imperial Interdicted Space).",
    ofNote: "Sector capital with extremely strict starport regulations — engine emissions, manifest checks, decontamination, even a counselor to discuss your ship's name. Radell Mining Corporation: largest sector company, hires freelancers at 75-300 cr/day. Rival ISD captains: Akal Zed (Stalker, brutal traditionalist) vs Tanda Pryl (Thunderflare, devious Force-sensitive, Dark Side Points 5). Moff Villis Andal: lazy, amused by their rivalry. Reputation system: newcomers face social penalties until proven."
