    lengthOfDay: "20 standard hours",
    lengthOfYear: "300 local days",
    sapientSpecies: "Zelosians (N)",
    starport: "1 standard class",
    population: "10 million",
    function: "Trade, mining",
    government: "Military dictatorship (Commander Galleros Nul)",
    techLevel: "Information",
    majorExports: "Raw ores",
    majorImports: "Weaponry, foodstuffs",
    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.246",
    summary: "Zelos II is home to the Zelosians — plant-based near-Humans with chlorophyll sap instead of blood, emerald green eyes, and complete night-blindness. They photosynthesize through their skin but can also eat normally. Zelosians are happy and energetic by day but fearful and suspicious at night. Alcohol has no effect on them, but refined sugar acts as an intoxicant. Commander Galleros Nul rules as a dictator-for-life under martial law, his power secured by his rare ability to venture outdoors at night. Unknown to Nul or the population, a full Imperial garrison hides in the Valley of Umbra — a permanently shadowed valley no Zelosian dares enter. A gravity well at the system's edge routinely yanks unsuspecting ships into the system. The dead literally walk at night due to 'jumper' parasites that reanimate corpses for hours.",
    locations: "Kryndyn (capital, 9M pop, Royal Palace with 100+ garrison, commodities market, bars/casinos/hotels). 5 smaller cities: Nul, Lyn, + 3 others, each with 10m walls, 6 gates, 1,000-troop garrisons. Valley of Umbra (permanently shadowed, secret Imperial garrison: 20 TIEs, 5 AT-ATs, 5 AT-STs, hundreds of troops, commanded by Major Luana Treftite). Railway/road network connects all cities. 4 moons: Bellatrig, Tanatrig, Moratrig, Nekotrig. Gravity well near Rymm (3rd planet, volcanic/unstable).",
    ofNote: "Zelosians: plant-based near-Humans, chlorophyll sap, night-blind (can't see below full moonlight), emerald green eyes, photosynthesize. Sugar = intoxicant, alcohol = no effect. Terrified of darkness — 'bad/dark/shadow/night' are curse words. Day of Sepulchral Night: solar eclipse + 3 visible moons = mass panic, store closures, possible suicide. Walking Dead: 'jumper' parasites reanimate week-old corpses for 1D hours (automatons, no consciousness, 4 wound levels to stop). Commander Nul: dictator-for-life (command 9D, DSP 4), can go outside at night, took power after 'Battle of Kryndyn' nocturnal predator attack 10 years ago. Imperial garrison in Valley of Umbra: completely unknown to Zelosians. Major Treftite: ambitious commander, wants the dead to keep walking to maintain population terror. Gravity well: failed piloting = hurtled into Zelos orbit. Aga: 4m nocturnal predators, rudimentary intelligence, use trees as clubs. Kilits: hair-covered raptors. Kro: red-eyed reptile packs that 'meep' when attacking."
