    majorExports: "Spice, laundered credits",
    majorImports: "Raw materials, equipment, shielding technology",
    aliases: ["Gallienis IV"],
    source: "WEG40075 Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations p.45-48",
    summary: "Originally called Gallienis IV, Bridin Anchorage was once a pleasant world rich in mineral deposits and famous for hundreds of kilometers of picturesque beaches. It was taken over by corrupt politician Quarlo Bridin, who fled Inner Rim corruption charges and convinced the frightened populace he could keep both Empire and New Republic at bay. By declaring itself a free and neutral planet, Bridin Anchorage became one of the most heavily shielded planets in the sector, impervious to all but the most determined assault. The price of this dubious freedom has been the rise of criminal organizations operating openly.",
    locations: "Planetary shield generators. Spice production facilities (Manliss Enterprise). Gambling establishments (Sehvorah's chain). Decaying urban slums (formerly a lush tourist world). Brandis Tech Institute (droid technology). Spaceport.",
    ofNote: "Headquarters of the Mandroxan cartel — a three-way alliance of the Manliss Enterprise (spice production, led by Artur Manliss), the Droxian Traders League (equipment and raw materials, led by the Herglic Sehvorah), and the Anavil Smugglers' Guild (spice distribution, led by Parmella Trillidor). Estimated 140,000+ individuals employed directly and indirectly through the cartel, with half again as many in casual or part-time roles. The Mandroxan cartel controls over two-thirds of all illegal spice production in the Portmoak sector, with agents in every major star system in the region across 23 star systems. The cartel operates in the full light of day, in open defiance of the law. Undercover law enforcement agents who are discovered routinely disappear. Independents who try to cut into the spice trade have their production centers bombed and personnel eliminated. The cartel's policy of criminal patronage guarantees employees protection from rival outsiders in exchange for unswerving loyalty. What was once a lush tourist world is now a collection of decaying slums where people fear going out at night. Gambling droids are everywhere and the populace is noted for their rudeness. Street children beg constantly."
