    terrain: "Forests, plains, grasslands",
    lengthOfDay: "24 standard hours",
    lengthOfYear: "364 local days",
    sapientSpecies: "Human (N), others",
    starport: "Imperial/Republic class",
    population: "2 billion (pre-destruction)",
    function: "Homeworld, academic",
    government: "Democracy",
    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "Wine, art, luxury goods",
    majorImports: "Manufactured goods, electronics",
    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.468",
    summary: "Alderaan was one of the most celebrated worlds in the galaxy — a verdant, temperate Core World renowned for its universities, cuisine, spiced wines, and traditions of dance, theater, music, and poetry. Human colonists arrived before the founding of the Republic, discovering a world abandoned by an insect species called the Killiks. Alderaan became a founding member of the Republic, and its cities were built to coexist with nature rather than dominate it. Three Alderaanian animal species — thrantas, grazers, and nerfs — spread throughout the galaxy over the centuries. After the horrors of the Clone Wars, Alderaan formally adopted pacifism and rid itself of all major weaponry. Under Bail Organa, this idealistic stance also served a political purpose, allowing Alderaan to oppose the New Order from within the Senate. When Bail's adopted daughter Leia Organa was caught receiving Rebel transmissions above Toprawa, Grand Moff Tarkin ordered the Death Star to destroy Alderaan as a demonstration of Imperial might. The planet was obliterated in an instant, killing 2 billion people. The Death Star was destroyed just days later, and Alderaan became a rallying cry for the Rebellion. What remains is an asteroid field called the Graveyard, orbited by the shattered remains of Alderaan's moon. Alderaan's sister world, Delaya, survived the destruction and remains the system's sole inhabited world — an agricultural planet of little galactic significance.",
    locations: "The Graveyard (asteroid field occupying Alderaan's former orbital position; orbited by remains of Alderaan's moon; pilgrimage site for Alderaanian survivors and exiles). Aldera (former capital city; destroyed 0 BBY). Delaya (surviving sister world in the Alderaan system; agricultural, light industry; refuge for Alderaanian survivors).",
    ofNote: "DESTROYED 0 BBY by the Death Star's superlaser on the order of Grand Moff Tarkin — the first use of the weapon, intended as a demonstration to subjugate restive Imperial worlds. The destruction killed all 2 billion inhabitants instantly. The Graveyard asteroid field is a memorial site; Alderaanian exiles make pilgrimages known as the Returnings to pay respects to the dead. Alderaan's pacifism meant no planetary shields or defense systems were in place at the time of destruction. Bail Organa (pre-destruction ruler) and Leia Organa (his adopted daughter, later Princess and Senator) were both active in covert Rebel support. Any campaign set before 0 BBY may feature Alderaan as a living world; campaigns set after should treat it as the Graveyard only. | GRAVEYARD OPERATIONS: Mining Outpost 11 in the asteroid field is garrisoned by Outpost 11 Stormtrooper squads and Outpost 11 Stormtrooper Officer commanders under Outpost 11 Imperial Officer leadership. The Another Chance — an Alderaanian armory ship drifting through the Graveyard on autopilot — is defended by Another Chance Labor Droid and Another Chance Repair Droid automated systems."
