    summary: "Shownar is a crystal planet of stunning natural beauty in Parmic Sector. Three large land masses are entirely composed of rare Vertag crystal, forming spires several kilometers tall that glow with faint blue light at night. Wind rushing between the spires at higher altitudes creates a haunting harmonic wave called the 'Shownar Lullaby.' Most spectacular is the planet's proximity to the Torch Nebula, an immense cloud of gases that fills Shownar's night sky with blue and red fire. Ruler Oro Freatt has turned Shownar into a trade and tourism nexus — his line of souvenir holocubes ('View of the Torch Nebula from the Nebula Hotel, Shownar') are ubiquitous among Core World tourists.",
    locations: "Nebula Hotel (renowned establishment with breathtaking views of the planet and Torch Nebula). Overcity (upper levels for moderate income and affluent tourists, 'family atmosphere'). Undercity (network of cheap memory-plastic buildings controlled by Freatt — smugglers and criminals meet to sell goods and services). Crystal spires (native Shownarri live inside them; Freatt's residence is also within a spire).",
    ofNote: "Local laws permit gambling and other vices. Law enforcement overlooks 'minor' smuggling but handles violent criminals harshly and cracks down on pickpockets. Freatt's organization controls specific industries (labor unions, food, transportation, communications, energy) — each criminal organization gets a sector while Freatt takes a percentage. He owns all property, collecting massive rents. The Imperial governor is bribed; income is underreported but enough goes to Imperial tax coffers to keep the sector government happy. Located in Parmic Sector near the Torch Nebula."
