    majorImports: "Labor (Hutt-supplied indentured servants), machinery, raw materials",
    source: "WEG40075 Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations p.31-37",
    summary: "Sabrix is the homeworld of the Sabrin Ring, a territorial criminal gang established by ex-Imperial Governor Miletta Sabrin after she fled Imperial space following the Battle of Endor. Located on an uncharted planet in the Samix sector, the Sabrixin system was settled using classified Imperial survey data. The population is largely composed of indentured laborers supplied by Hutt sources, refugees, and assorted criminal elements.",
    locations: "Radioactive mines (multiple open-pit and underground operations across the planet), Sabrin Ring headquarters, starport and repair facilities (available to allied pirates at nominal cost). Sister planets Helisk and Elokas also settled with Hutt-imported labor.",
    ofNote: "The Sabrin Ring controls three populated planets in the Sabrixin system with an estimated 4,000+ gang members. The operation runs on a cycle: Hutt-supplied indentured laborers mine radioactive ores, which are shipped via smugglers to processing plants throughout the Rim. Profits are laundered through legitimate businesses on other Rim planets and reinvested in purchasing more labor. Lady Sabrin is slowly refining radioactives into bomb-grade material to extort protection from neighboring systems. Pirates enjoy free passage through the system in exchange for supplying machinery and raw materials. Taxes are collected at blasterpoint, and failure to pay earns a one-way trip to the mines. Exit permits are prohibitively expensive, trapping most of the population."
