    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.117",
    summary: "Farrfin was a popular refuge of smugglers and pirates in the days of the Old Republic. Its remote location made it ideal for hiding from pursuers, and eventually the Rebel Alliance made use of the planet as well. The Farghul, a species easily given to smuggling and con artistry, freely welcomed all newcomers — if only for the chance to bilk the unwary out of every credit they could. The planet is medium-sized with high mountain peaks, deep valleys, some tectonic instability, and underground streams. These streams meet with lava just beneath the surface, causing huge fissures of steam to explode from the ground. These 'steam storms' make the planet difficult for the Empire to cope with: the damp weather, low visibility, and treacherous terrain have all contributed to making Imperial occupation extremely difficult.",
    locations: "Farlhu (major city). Jahhnu (major city; home of the famed Jahhnu betting houses, which rake in incredible sums as gullible off-worlders and bored smugglers gamble away their earnings). Geltyu (major city).",
    ofNote: "Imperial forces have tried to dominate the Farrfin system and have met with stern resistance. The craggy, fog-choked planet makes ground operations difficult, and the Farghul, used to operating in these conditions, have managed to stall Imperial takeover. The New Republic is supplying weapons, food, and medicine so the Farghul can continue their resistance. A strong criminal element thrives in all three cities — con-artists run sabacc scams on every street corner and pockets are picked left and right. That this haven for bored criminals has managed to repulse Imperial attacks is bewildering to the Empire."
