    summary: "Hijarna has been a mystery to xenoarcheologists galaxy-wide since its discovery during the Fifth Alderaanian Expedition. The planet is almost totally devoid of life, and if all the data on its structure and composition is accurate, Hijarna was destroyed by warfare. Fossil records indicate an abundance of animal life at one time, but no trace remains of the sapient species responsible for the destruction. The cause of Hijarna's downfall has remained a topic of speculation for decades — theories range from alien invasion from another galaxy, to a super-virus created by the natives, to a temporal rift that sucked all life from the surface.",
