    summary: "New Cov is a planet where the dangers of the environment are the source of its economic value. Home to numerous sentient exotic plants that produce biomolecules — important manufacturing components that cannot be synthesized, needed for synthesized medicines and some partially organic industrial processes. However, the plants take great exception to harvesting — they have been known to eat the occasional careless molecule harvester, and the reason the cities are armored and domed is to prevent the plants from infiltrating or casting spores. Despite the danger, economics rule out, and the Covies are building two more cities to increase living space and processing facilities.",
    locations: "Ilic (the great walled city; one of eight armored, domed cities built in the jungles; the tops poke through the clutching trees like silver-skinned droid domes dropped into green quicksand; visiting ships enter through vents near the top, large enough to admit anything up to a W-class space barge; ships follow curved pipes down to a bright landing area beneath a transparisteel dome; professional greeters welcome visitors with data card maps). Seven Other Walled Cities (similar armored and domed jungle cities for living space and biomolecule processing).",
    ofNote: "All residents are employees of the New Cov Biomolecule Company and earn high pay for their dangerous efforts. The planet is allied with the New Republic but makes periodic tributes to the Empire in the form of sanctioned Imperial raids — the Empire takes whatever refined biomolecules it needs, leaves, and New Cov remains in the good graces of both governments. Inbound customs are a mere formality since the cities depend on ships to export goods; outbound scrutiny is much tighter."
