    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.124",
    summary: "The super-hot planet Nkllon orbits the intense sun of Athega. Once it was thought the rich raw materials locked within the planet would never be freed — Nkllon orbits so close to its sun that any normal ship approaching has its hull quickly peeled away by the intense heat. Only through specially-designed shieldships can a normal ship reach the planet. The sunlit side is off-limits to even Lando's well-prepared operation, but with the use of Nomad City and Nkllon's very slow rotation, the dark side remains cool enough to work on. The lights of radio-controlled mole miners can be seen shining out of the darkness like close stars as they dig up the surface.",
    locations: "Nomad City (huge, humpbacked mobile mining complex that constantly moves across the surface, staying within the planet's protective shadow; built from castaway vehicles — an old Dreadnaught-class cruiser captured after the Battle of Endor, fitted atop 40 captured Imperial AT-AT Walkers for mobility; thousands of lights blaze over its surface; sweeping searchlights scan the ground as it lumbers over craters; a handful of tiny escort shuttles and pilot craft fly around it directing its trek). Mole Miner Operations (radio-controlled mining vehicles that dig up the dark side surface).",
    ofNote: "The brainchild of Lando Calrissian, based on plans he found in Lord Ecclessis Figg's personal logs for a rolling mining center on Bespin's inner planet Miser (Figg abandoned the idea because Miser's terrain was too difficult for wheels; Lando used legs instead). The operation was a huge success until the Empire stole 51 mole miners for use in the Sluis Van campaign. Lando has left Nomad City to extract revenge upon the Empire. The view on approach is absolutely stunning — its sweeping lights and lumbering form fills the darkside night with a spectacular glow."
