    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.128",
    summary: "Pantolomin is a galactic paradise. The closest planet to the Panto sun, it orbits at a comfortable distance and supports a huge number of life forms. Eighty percent of the planet is covered in deep blue water, with three large continents (Tralla, Kossi, and Brint), five major islands, and hundreds of small islands — all jungle paradises of thick rain forests. The underwater coral reefs are renowned throughout the galaxy for their unique beauty. The planet's native race, the amphibious Lomins, have created a luxury world that thrives on tourism, producing luxury goods that sell for exorbitant prices throughout the galaxy. Cities are coastal and designed to blend into the natural beauty, with beaches and deep forest left in a natural state.",
    locations: "Coral Vanda (luxury submersible casino cruise ship making three and seven day excursions through the huge coral reef network off the coast of Tralla; eight gambling rooms each as huge and ornate as the next, filled with sabacc tables, lugjack bars, tregald booths, holo-game tables, warp-top booths; multi-species bar bisects each room; full-wall transparisteel hulls separate each casino from the ocean beyond, revealing schools of brilliantly-colored fish, sea mammals, and winding forests of coral). Tralla (northern continent; coast features the coral reef network). Kossi (continent). Brint (continent). Panto Prime (deep space station orbiting between Pantolomin and Toloran; luxury resort and casino doubling as a functional spaceport). Toloran (second planet; cold world of snow and mountains; repulsor skiing, hover sledding, wilderness survival camps; Snow Nara ice barge sails the great ice floes of the northern reaches). Atloran (third planet; lifeless sphere with seven zero-gee space camps surrounding a modern spaceport).",
    ofNote: "The entire Panto system has been established as a resort — from Pantolomin's tropical climes to Toloran's wintery wonderland to Atloran's zero-gee camps. The Lomins share governing duties on the tourist board with the Tolos of Toloran. The Coral Vanda is billed as the most impressive and luxurious casino in the galaxy, and no one has ever challenged that claim. The sights beyond the transparisteel walls are breathtaking — rippling blue-green water sparkles in the ship's running lights, revealing huge schools of brilliantly-colored fish and winding forests of coral in wondrous patterns of loops and fans."
