    summary: "Poderis can best be described as 'marginal.' Virtually no one has ever heard of this small colony planet. The colony should have been declared a failure and relocated decades ago, but the stubborn nature of the colonists has kept it going. Its disorienting 10-hour days, unusual geography, and violent winds make it a singularly difficult location to survive in. Poderis has a nearly perpendicular axial tilt, creating terrible hurricane-level winds during spring and autumn. The 'lowland-slough ecology' and erosion patterns have created towering mesas lying in archipelagos dotting large oceans.",
