    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.130",
    summary: "The hot sun of Rish has four planets. Only the third, Rishi, supports life. The only viable places to live — as far as human and alien colonists are concerned — are a handful of deep valleys. Living conditions are quite crowded, with colonists in low-lying swamps while the native Rishii live among the high mountain peaks. The colonists belong to the fundamentalist H'kig religion, who purchased two colony ships seventy years ago during an Old Republic colonization push and came to Rishi as a haven of religious freedom. Each city-vale is composed of cream-white stone buildings. Far up in the mountain peaks live the loose avian tribes of native Rishii, who have a peaceful relationship with the colonists but don't understand why the wingless ones want to live in the hottest spots.",
    locations: "City-Vales (cream-white stone settlements in deep valleys; some buildings constructed in the craggy mountains, but mountaintops are left alone for the Rishii). Rishii Mountain Nests (avian tribal settlements in the highest peaks). Karrde's Base (smuggler Talon Karrde maintained a base on Rishi, used after his Myrkr base was compromised).",
    ofNote: "The H'kig religion was founded by a religious leader on the Core World of Galand who was martyred for preaching against the Viceroy. After centuries of persecution, his followers colonized Rishi. The theocratic government has established laws based on religious beliefs — specific laws forbid repulsorlifts before first meal and after last prayer. Strict standards of propriety concerning clothing, hair length, and social mores apply in public. First offenses get a warning and small fine; multiple offenders may be banished; capital crimes (murder, kidnapping, grand theft) can carry death sentences. The colonists remain neutral in the Imperial/NR conflict and allow anyone to trade fairly with them. Many underworld organizations have established bases here because of this tolerance. Bounty hunters followed Karrde to Rishi seeking a huge Thrawn-decreed bounty; most left empty-handed."
