    summary: "Sluis Van is the primary star system in the Sluis sector, an active member of the New Republic and the site of an extensive deep-space shipyard and docking facility. The facility regularly has about 100 medium-sized or larger vessels in transit and comprises the largest shipyards in its section of the galaxy. The Sluissi run an efficient, respectable operation handling commercial traffic for the sector and long-haul ships, with an open contract allowing any Republic military or diplomatic ships to use the yards.",
    locations: "Orbit Docks (dozens upon dozens of docking facilities; some built for large capital ships, others for small freighters, a few for the largest container ships). Multi-Docks (like Orbit Dock V-475 — Rendili StarDrive Space Dock, 4,846 meters long, crew 9,500; feature one or two large capital ship dry docks, hangar bays for smaller craft, and docking tubes for freighters; multi-leveled entertainment facilities in their centers with motel cubes, space-stop cafes, cantinas, holovid/live entertainment, and dock markets). Central Administration Space Station (shipyard control center). Perimeter Battle Stations (armored defense platforms with turbolaser batteries, proton torpedo ports, and tractor beam projectors; limited maneuverability; can handle pirate raids but not a full offensive).",
    ofNote: "There were 112 transient warships in the system when Grand Admiral Thrawn launched his attack. The ships were gathering into a convoy to bring support to the battered Bpfassh system after Imperial hit-and-fade attacks. Sixty-five warships had been pressed into cargo carriers with the remaining ships on escort duty. Though many Republic ships were damaged, Thrawn's plan to steal the vessels met with failure. Shuttles constantly ferry spacers between Sluis Van and the orbit docks; tugs guide capital ships past space lane marker buoys to waiting bays."
