    summary: "Trogan is a planet of harsh contrasts: natural beauty marred by violent weather, areas of lush vegetation springing up among vast tracts of barren wasteland. Perhaps best known for its tides — the gravitational pull of three moons makes for impressive tidal shifts. The coastlines are heavily eroded and subject to pounding weather and the inexorable pull of the ocean. The planet's ocean activity during seasonal high tide can be quite spectacular, especially during violent electrical storms.",
