    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.135",
    summary: "Ukio is one of the best-known agricultural planets in the Abrion sector and one of the most efficient food distribution centers in its region. A large planet with gentle winds, calm weather, and a mild climate, seasonal changes are virtually nonexistent due to slow rotation and low axial tilt — the growing season lasts most of the Ukian year. Once a planet of rolling hills and wild grasses, decades of scientific harvest improvement have transformed Ukio into carefully cultivated and painstakingly designed field systems systematically farmed for maximum output. Three major continents are cut through by hundreds of rivers providing ample natural irrigation, enhanced by modern technology to redirect rivers and increase irrigation capacity.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "Crop rotation procedures are not only recommended but required by Ukian law. The Ukian government displays remarkable foresight in preventing the destruction of arable land — all Ukians must ensure they do not exhaust the growing potential of the soil. The planet has ample fallow land for future expansion. Ukians are tall, reedy people. The Overliege is Gol dosLa, with his eldest son Tol dosLa serving as spokesman — a soft-spoken but shrewd political operator known for gently persuading people to his point of view."
