    summary: "Woostri is a predominantly ocean planet with a single small continent. Woostoid historians claim that before a great cataclysm long ago, a substantial portion of the surface was above water. Most of the continent has been transformed into a single, sprawling urban technopolis. Woostri is a major administrative asset to the New Republic — the computer processing facilities and the natural organizational ability of the Woostoids makes it an ideal 'data-crunching facility' for the fledgling government. A large number of NeuroSaav Model 608 Mega p'uters have been installed in Gopsthal, the main administrative district. As a result, much of the planet is now computer-controlled — everything from landspeeder maintenance to traffic control to housekeeping — giving Woostoids a large amount of free time devoted to entertainment.",
    locations: "Gopsthal (main administrative district; houses the NeuroSaav Model 608 Mega p'uter installations that run most of the planet's functions). Woostri HoloScan Database (holographic library hailed as one of the most complete research facilities in the galaxy; huge complex thousands of kilometers across and several hundred stories tall; access for a few credits per visit; information on civilizations predating the Old Republic, scientific research, star travel, and millions of other topics). New Republic War College Branch Campus (located near the HoloScan Database research facility).",
    ofNote: "The planet boasts an incredible selection of music complexes, holo-theatres, restaurants, sporting events, and amusement parks. Though the Woostoids never intended to become a tourist attraction, they welcome the diversity of countless species who come to recreate. The HoloScan Database draws a large number of off-world visitors and scholars at any given hour."
