    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.137",
    summary: "Xa Fel, in the Kanchin sector, is one of Kuat Drive Yards' major manufacturing facilities, producing fully 20 percent of the corporation's inventory of starship hyperdrive engines. Once a world of sprawling plains and gentle hills with fertile agricultural land, KDY converted it to manufacturing by exploiting the technologically primitive native Xa Fel — awing them with Imperial technology and convincing them to sell land rights cheaply through flattery, bribery, and strong-arm tactics. The Xa Fel soon found themselves tenants on their own land. Factory complexes and corporate worker dormitories now dominate a dreary, polluted landscape.",
    locations: "KDY Factory Complexes (hyperdrive engine manufacturing facilities covering the former plains). Corporate Worker Dormitories (housing for KDY workforce).",
    ofNote: "Under KDY management, the planet has been steadily despoiled by pollution. The air has become mildly acidic due to chemical pollution — during the rainy season, improperly protected buildings may be severely damaged and corroded. Under New Republic rule, the NR ordered KDY to clean up the planet, but KDY bureaucrats have slowed cleanup to a crawl. Attacks from Grand Admiral Thrawn forced the Republic to concentrate on preventing the Empire from retaking the planet, leaving KDY unsupervised. Xa Fel was a prime target for Thrawn — the ability to snatch pre-made starship stardrives was a tremendous boost to the Imperial shipbuilding effort."
