    summary: "Vo Dasha is the single moon of the gas giant Taboon, named by its owner, Bogga the Hutt. Its Type II atmosphere prevents prolonged unprotected exposure, so Bogga constructed a hermetically sealed fortress atop one of the moon's most prominent mountain peaks. From this citadel he directs all of his criminal operations throughout the Stenness Node. The fortress is a full-featured base: meeting chambers, storage areas, docking and maintenance bays, weapons lockers, living quarters for staff and guards, a substantial dungeon complex for prisoners, and a throne room and audience chamber where Bogga holds court.",
    locations: "Bogga's Citadel (hermetically sealed fortress atop a prominent mountain peak; includes meeting chambers, storage areas, docking and maintenance bays, weapons lockers, living quarters, dungeon complex, and throne room/audience chamber). Docking bays (capable of receiving small to medium ships; primary access point for the citadel). Dungeon complex (sizeable prisoner holding area beneath the main citadel).",
    ofNote: "4000 BBY (Tales of the Jedi era). Bogga the Hutt (4000 BBY), Grimorg (4000 BBY), and Bogga's Thugs (4000 BBY) are based here. The citadel population of ~250 consists of Bogga's guards, enforcers, servants, and criminal associates. The moon's hostile atmosphere and remote location make it a natural stronghold — visitors must be cleared through Bogga's organization to land."
