    techLevel: "Feudal",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "High technology, especially weapons",
    source: "WEG40082 Tales of the Jedi Companion",
    summary: "Onderon is a forested world in the Japrael system of the Stenness Node, long ruled by an isolationist monarchy that repeatedly refused Republic membership — until now. Four moons orbit it in wildly varying paths; the closest, Dxun, periodically comes near enough for an atmosphere bridge to form, allowing Dxun's native warbeasts to migrate to the planet during summer months. The great walled city of Iziz — covering more than a thousand square miles and housing several million inhabitants — grew from the need to defend against those same warbeasts. Onderonians who were exiled from Iziz built their own strongholds in the forested wilderness and gradually developed a symbiotic bond with the warbeasts, earning the name 'beast-riders.' The resulting Beast Wars raged for centuries before Jedi Knights intervened. Queen Galia, first of her line to break free of the dark side influence that had corrupted her ancestors, and her husband the beast lord Odon Kira now rule Onderon in relative peace and have applied for Republic membership.",
    locations: "Iziz (the great walled city; covers more than 1,000 square miles; population of several million; the dominant population center of Onderon — see Onderon - Iziz). Forested wilderness (home to exiled beast-riders and their warbeat allies; vast stretches of forest beyond the city walls). Dxun (the closest moon; periodically forms an atmosphere bridge with Onderon during summer; home to warbeasts and the sealed Sith tomb — see Onderon - Dxun).",
    ofNote: "4000 BBY (Tales of the Jedi era). Queen Galia and Odon Kira jointly rule. Jedi Master Arca Jeth (4000 BBY) is the Jedi watchman of the Onderon system. The dark side corrupted every monarch in Galia's line before her. Beast-riders are considered criminals and exiles by Iziz society but have proven formidable warriors. Onderon is in the process of joining the Galactic Republic at this time.\n\nRandom Encounter Table (Stenness Node jump points — roll 5D): 5–6 Astrogation Survey Team; 7–8 Bounty Hunter; 9–11 Criminal; 12–13 Diplomat; 14 Force-user; 15–16 Information Broker; 17 Jedi Knight; 18–19 Jump Beacon Patrol; 20 Local Military Craft; 21–22 Passenger Transport; 23 Pirate; 24 Republic Battlegroup; 25 Rocket-jumper Patrol; 26–27 Smuggler; 28–30 Trader. For well-traveled routes, randomly select several entries."
