    majorImports: "None",
    source: "WEG40082 Tales of the Jedi Companion",
    summary: "Dxun is the closest of Onderon's four moons, orbiting in a path that at its nearest point allowed a temporary atmosphere bridge to form between moon and planet. During Onderon's summer season, native Dxun creatures — particularly the fearsome warbeasts — crossed this bridge onto Onderon, driving the Onderonians to build the walled city of Iziz for protection. After the Beast Wars ended, Dxun remains wild and dangerous. The moon now serves as the burial site of Onderon's dark side rulers: the sarcophagi of King Ommin, Queen Amanoa, and the ancient Sith Lord Freedon Nadd lie within a deep tomb sealed by the light side of the Force and guarded by warbeasts. Jedi Master Arca Jeth monitors the tomb closely, fearing Sith devotees may attempt to steal the sarcophagi and release the spirits of the entombed dark siders.",
    locations: "Tomb of Freedon Nadd (deep underground vault containing the sarcophagi of King Ommin, Queen Amanoa, and the ancient Sith Lord Freedon Nadd; sealed by the light side of the Force; guarded by warbeasts; Arca Jeth monitors it closely against Sith interference). Warbeat territories (vast jungle ranges prowled by Dxun's native warbeasts, including the massive creatures that once crossed the atmosphere bridge to Onderon).",
    ofNote: "4000 BBY (Tales of the Jedi era). The sarcophagi of King Ommin (4000 BBY), Queen Amanoa (4000 BBY), and Freedon Nadd (4000 BBY) are entombed here. Arca Jeth fears Sith devotees will attempt to retrieve the sarcophagi — GMs should treat this as an ongoing threat. Dxun's atmosphere bridge to Onderon is seasonal and temporary; it does not currently exist year-round."
