    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "Foodstuffs, high tech, weaponry",
    source: "WEG40071 Dark Empire Sourcebook p.81",
    summary: "Byss was the secret capital of the Emperor's revived Empire, a mythic world bathed in the Dark Side of the Force in the heart of the Deep Core. Orbiting a binary system of a blue star and blue dwarf companion, Byss is bathed in soothing blue-green sunlight which fluoresces the microscopic life in lake and river chains dotting the surface. Mild seasons result from a minuscule axial tilt and a very stable geologic foundation. Storms, volcanism or other violent phenomena are extremely rare. Covered by wind-smoothed plateaus and canyons, this world is legendary for the calming and reputedly invigorating effect of its balmy climate. When the Emperor chose this world for his private reserve, no expense was spared — his personal architectural staff was granted carte blanche to build a citadel to Palpatine's hubris. Slaves and machinery were brought by specially trained space pilots using encoded astrogation systems to reach Byss. Soon the planet gleamed with oddly shaped and ornate towers and complexes. Enormous leisure and habitation complexes were included in the original designs, as Palpatine planned for millions to permanently reside here, where he and his minions could use their Dark Side skills to feed off their life energy. A legend was created of a mystic siren world whose surreal shores and glimmering oceans held the promise of contentment unattainable anywhere else. Millions applied for visas to this mysterious world, but few ever suspected Byss lay in the Deep Core itself. Imperial Intelligence painstakingly sifted innumerable dossiers to find those most suited to the Emperor's needs, and a few million per month were chosen and transported to Byss in secret. Upon arrival, they live out the rest of their lives in harmless amusements and pageants, all communications to loved ones censored to perpetuate the myth and secrecy of this distant world.",
    locations: "Imperial Citadel (sprawling fortress at the center of the Imperial control sector; the dark heart of Palpatine's New Order; an ominous black spire looming several kilometers above the security zone; maze-like halls contain all facilities and computer systems necessary to command the Empire including HoloNet communication modules, subspace transceivers and comm systems; lower levels contain a personal audience chamber, viewing rooms and palatial private apartments; private landing bay, baths, barracks for three legions of stormtroopers, 400 Sovereign Protectors and 600 Sentinels; guest space for dozens of Imperial Advisors; gladiatorial arenas, mock combat tank, libraries, museums, internal gardens, menagerie of exotic beasts; dungeon equipped with interrogation tools where the revived Inquisitorius is based). Clone Labs (deep inside the Imperial Citadel; full library of Dark Side texts for the Emperor's personal study; private meditation chamber with small rest cubicle; collection rooms filled with ancient works of art, holo-tapestries, fine mosaics, and the Emperor's collection of lightsabers taken from Jedi he has killed; Clone Vat Chamber at center with at least a dozen clones in various states of growth floating in nutrient tanks, tended by Clone Keepers and their leader, the Constable of Homunculi). Imperial Freight Complex (three-kilometer-wide tower reaching from ground level to low orbit, 168 kilometers up, tethered to an orbital satellite with repulsorlift generators; military staging area, refueling depot and stopover station; hundreds of ships arrive hourly; security is very tight with Hunter-Killer probe droids and Guardian-class patrol ships). Byss Bistro (popular spacer dive located near the docking cradles in the Freight Complex's spacer zone; eclectic menu for any species; freelance spacers negotiate deals and trade stories here).",
    ofNote: "DARK SIDE NEXUS: The entire planet is bathed in the Dark Side of the Force, serving as the Emperor's seat of power. The populace's life energy is secretly drained by the Emperor and his Dark Side Adepts. | IMPERIAL CONTROL SECTOR: Deceptive paradise of colorful plazas and public buildings camouflaging a massively armed and shielded defensive zone; shipyards, fighter bases and military barracks for an entire army; every building dotted with defense turbolasers and shock fields. | ACCESS: Requires encoded astrogation systems — the planet's Deep Core location is a closely guarded secret. No rare elements or heavy metals present. Native life is largely nocturnal. Five moons with little tidal influence."
