    source: "WEG40071 Dark Empire Sourcebook p.87",
    summary: "Da Soocha means 'Waking Planet' in Huttese and refers to a vast planet-covering ocean. The ocean itself was alive and gifted with godlike intelligence, according to Hutt legend. Early in their history, the Hutts saw the Cyax star and created legends about it and its planets. As Hutts began leaving Varl, they set out to explore other systems but left Cyax alone — it was better to allow the myths to remain. Da Soocha does not show up on Hutt astrogation charts, with a notable exception: Jabba himself had the coordinates in his databases. Some think he planned to build a new floating palace there. After his demise, Da Soocha would have remained an obscure myth were it not for R2-D2, who infiltrated Jabba's computers. Once at Sullust, the droid gave the system coordinates to the Rebellion's officers and Rebel scouts investigated. The planet is indeed covered by a vast ocean with no sign of intelligent life found, though surveys were admittedly brief. Admiral Ackbar chose Da Soocha as a potential refuge for the Mon Calamari people after the attacks on their homeworld. Only the most cursory examinations beneath the surface have been made, and it is still a mystery what life exists there.",
    locations: "",
