    source: "WEG40071 Dark Empire Sourcebook p.87",
    summary: "The Pinnacle Moon is the fifth moon of Da Soocha in the Cyax system, chosen by the New Republic as their command base after the fall of Coruscant. Its location had never been registered on the Haven list, which had fallen into Imperial hands. Billions of years ago, powerful volcanic eruptions spewed superheated minerals high into the air. The effect of Da Soocha's heavy gravity combined with the moon's light gravity created immense tidal forces which washed away sedimentary layers of soil, leaving the distinctive pinnacles. Many kilometers high, these pillars were hollowed out by erosion, and many forms of plant and animal life live inside these columns, creating the illusion of a sparse, desolate world. One unique effect of Da Soocha V's environment is that nearly all higher forms can fly. The most highly evolved are the Ixlls, small intelligent mammals inhabiting the upper strata of the columns. With fusion drills, technicians cut into the few lifeless columns and built the Republic's facilities there.",
    locations: "Pinnacle Base (New Republic command base built inside hollowed-out pinnacle columns using fusion drills; served as the secret headquarters after the evacuation of Coruscant; housed Republic strategic command, military leadership including Mon Mothma and Admiral Ackbar, and fighter squadrons).",
    ofNote: "PINNACLE BASE COMPROMISED: With the final assault of the Empire, Pinnacle Base's location is no longer a secret and the Rebel Alliance is now trying to find an appropriate location for a new command base. | UNIQUE ENVIRONMENT: Nearly all higher life forms on this moon are capable of flight due to the light gravity. The Ixlls are capable of true flight at Move 28 (~80 KMH) in their home planet's low gravity; in regular gravity they can glide without powered flight."
