    locations: "StarForge Shipyard (capable of constructing or repairing any ship up to the size of a small cruiser). Casino (entertainment district). Cyberdocs (cybernetic modification facilities). Arms Dealers (weapons merchants). Warehouses (dozens of storage facilities). Repair Bays (ship maintenance and overhaul). Permanent Living Quarters (residential section).",
    ofNote: "RULES: Murder (cold-blooded, not self-defense), unwarranted assault, and theft are punished by execution (murder) or exile. A small security force enforces these few rules. | SURVIVAL: High on the Imperial Locate and Destroy list. The StarForge Nebula is a vast, sensor-muddling, comm-jamming cloud of seething matter. The Station moves periodically and puts out passive sensor buoys to detect visitors. Finding it is virtually impossible without assistance — the Far Orbit took days even with an Alliance chart. To destroy it would require a massive naval sweep. Administrative complacency, lack of military force, and widespread bribes to Imperial officials have kept it safe, though newly appointed Moff Irnst Staweld may change that. | DEFENSES: A knockoff light customs corvette and a squadron of six Y-wings. All tenants contribute to Station upkeep and defense. Several Shipyard products have gone into the defense force over the years."
