    source: "WEG40062 Wanted by Cracken p.72",
    summary: "Gormdin is a temperate moon orbiting the gas giant Sarrelon IV. It is the only habitable body in the Sarrelon system, which comprises six planets each with several moons. Four oceans cover 60% of Gormdin's surface; the land masses are covered by plains, forests (trees only one and a half to two meters tall), and plateaus. The plateaus support small forested areas where Gormdin's natural inhabitants, the Gorms, are found. The moon now serves as the hidden base of the terrorist Lohn Genden.",
    locations: "Genden's Base (located within a network of caves beneath one of the many plateaus; entrance at the edge of the plateau, accessible only by starship or airspeeder).",
    ofNote: "SARRELON SYSTEM DATA: Star: Sarrelon (orange). Orbital bodies: Sarrelon I (searing rock, 2 moons), Sarrelon II (desolate searing rock, 3 moons), Sarrelon III (gas giant, 5 moons), Sarrelon IV (gas giant, 8 moons — Gormdin orbits here), Sarrelon V (gas giant, 12 moons), Sarrelon VI (frozen rock, 2 moons). | GENDEN'S FORCES: Approximately 50 terrorists (Humans, Twi'leks, Rodians, Gamorreans). Fleet: 5 light freighters, 2 Lambda-class shuttles, 3 Z-95 Headhunter starfighters, 2 transport ships, 10 airspeeders (2 passengers each)."
