    source: "WEG40083 Classic Adventures p.50",
    summary: "Cairn is a city on Seikosha controlled by competing crimelords, primarily Janelle Serap and her rival Lydenn Carridon. The city serves as a landing point for off-world traders and smugglers bringing in contraband goods.",
    locations: "Event Horizon (a cramped, dimly lit, dingy spacers' bar with a crude 'No droids' sign outside — frequented by the dregs of a hundred worlds, guilty of various crimes in virtually every star system; a Twi'lek tends bar while patrons finger illegal weapons; the back booth is used for clandestine meetings).",
    ofNote: "Cairn is defended by four modified Z-95 Mark II Headhunter starfighters flown by Cairn Headhunter Pilot crews. The city is contested between crimelord Janelle Serap and her rival Lydenn Carridon, who employs Cairn Gamorrean Thug enforcers. Drebbick's Henchman operatives serve ISB agent Chiron Drebbick who has infiltrated Carridon's organization. Jasta Finn's Henchman thugs and Carridon's Hired Gun mercenaries also operate in the city."
