    function: "Processing metals/minerals",
    government: "Participatory democracy",
    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "Processed alloys, Trell leather",
    majorImports: "Raw material, foodstuffs",
    source: "WEG40139 Cracken's Threat Dossier p.122",
    summary: "Trellar Yagen is the third planet in the Bovo Yagen system, named after one of Captain Yagen's sons. It is a sweltering jungle planet filled with many carnivorous fauna and flora. One of the most famous predators is the Trell, a small but vicious jungle predator known for its incredible speed in darting through the trees — difficult to catch even for Bovorian eyes and ears. The leather made from Trell skin is incredibly soft and supple, and is highly prized by well-to-do store owners.",
    locations: "Processing Plant (human-operated facility where raw metals from the Tava Yagen asteroid belt are made ready for spaceship production and prismatic crystals are broken down and polished).",
    ofNote: "18 ABY (Cracken's Threat Dossier): Humans set up a processing plant on Trellar Yagen in agreement with the Bovorians, who refused to allow the loud industrial machinery on their homeworld of Bovo Yagen due to their sensitive hearing. The humans gladly accepted Trellar Yagen as the base of processing operations. Bovorians enjoy hunting Trell on this planet, though they must wear specialized ear protection to save their hearing, which further increases the difficulty of the hunt."
