    source: "WEG40139 Cracken's Threat Dossier p.127",
    summary: "Drall is a planet with lighter gravity than most humans are accustomed to, but it suits the native Drall just fine. The axial tilt causes one small enclosed water mass to actually boil during summers — called the Boiling Sea, it is replenished during the hard, cold winter. This quiet, pretty world is the homeworld of the Drall — a dignified, learned species of scholars and scientists.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "18 ABY (Cracken's Threat Dossier): During the height of trade prior to the war, Drall may have been a planet of tourism for outsiders, but it was still the residence of Drall as well as humans and Selonians. As tempers rose and tension increased between the species, more Drall returned to their homeworld from other planets as the humans and Selonians left it to return to theirs. The Drall remain amicable and respectful to other species, but do not go out of their way to socialize. | The planetary repulsor on Drall played a critical role during the Corellian Incident — scientists on Drall used it to counteract Centerpoint Station's beam, preventing the destruction of the Bovo Yagen system."
