    summary: "Deep in the StarForge Nebula in Ado sector, a planetoid-based shadowport that has grown from a smuggler's refuge into a thriving illegal station. Founded 70 years ago by Muo Glandish, who was eventually killed by an old enemy. Now governed by a tenant council that elects an administrator.",
    locations: "StarForge Shipyard (Run by Chidee Na Maak, a Duros starshipwright. Three spacedocks with a three-month wait list. Construction takes one week per hull die at double new cost. Cash up front, no bargaining. Work guaranteed. Specializes in knockoff combat starships and custom designs). Station Facilities (Medium freighter and small capital ship berths, dozens of warehouses, repair bays, cyberdocs, arms dealers, restaurants, a casino, and permanent living quarters). Defense Force (Small force including a Skipray 12h blastboat and a Corellian gunship, rotated as newer ships become available).",
    ofNote: "The Station moves periodically to evade patrols — sometimes with only an hour's warning. New location spread by word of mouth. 20,000 credit standing bounty on snitches. Murder (except fair fights), assault, and theft punished by execution or permanent exile. | The StarForge Nebula is vast, sensor-muddling, and comm-jamming, making the Station extremely hard to find even when you know where to look. Navigating local space requires slow movement through planetoid fields. | Notable for the StarForge Shipyards — an excellent potential source of light combat ships. The station is mobile, a necessary precaution against Imperial patrols."
